MOLETSENE Makoti is a heartbroken man. This is because he feels the justice system has let him down and no one cares about him.   The 36-year-old from Makapanstad in North West told Daily Sun his problems with the police started in 2008 when he went to open an assault case against his neighbour and was sent home without being helped.   He said every time he went to the local police station to report cases, the cops refused to even listen to what he had to say. He said they laughed at him and made jokes about him.  if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsuG7W1BYYuUDQciVS2-84p1ii0eyt07tn8hZeoW5B72jS6lLdm2u4vBzdfCtNOkY5Sh4Wde_LElvgQlSxUV-phMEffOuQAQrNYGv8YqPUZUc5TR-a_E9TkKf304DwTMrrUQHvB4WwPKgo1J9_pfU63nN3askFhiOuLYeXr1y0STgCa7ombqvS9kKTWelieo2k0cG_2jFvNAgqNq-SPAGj-8F8IrLA88Esn-j0Lae6r1ExWQHORGi6t0OaEgMrqF0oSpQn2l92ysz7L4iaD_v74UtfJu-tM\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzHofGmT-NczZEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
